parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
grinding or screeching sounds are heard
the brake light comes on
and the vehicle may not stop or slow down as expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The constant moisture build-up in the headlights can cause them to burn out, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Headlights burn out frequently
often without warning
and can be expensive to repair or replace.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Gauge Malfunction and Electrical Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty fuel gauge can cause the driver to become stranded, and the erratic electrical issues can lead to a loss of power and safety features.
symptoms: Fuel gauge displays incorrect readings
sudden drops in fuel level
no lights on the dashboard
and loss of power after disconnection of the battery.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Light and Grinding Noise Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty brake system can cause the brake light to come on unnecessarily, leading to a loss of confidence in the brakes and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake light comes on while driving
grinding noise when applying brakes under 40mph
and intermittent brake light issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty airbag module can cause the airbag light to flash, disabling the airbags and increasing the risk of injury in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Airbag light flashes
internal shorting of the airbag module
and disablement of airbags.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Suspension and Steering System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension and steering system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or over irregular road surfaces.
symptoms: The vehicle's rear end bounces and sways
the steering wheel shimmies and shakes
the vehicle feels like it's about to lose control
the steering wheel must be held with two hands
the rear end feels like it's jumping and about to separate from the front end.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The brakes start to skip
the vehicle's brakes fail to engage properly
the vehicle's brakes are unresponsive.
